08/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic and two other officials will have to pay a fine of 417 euros each for drinking champagne at a stadium following Serbia's victory over Romania in a World Cup qualifier in October, local media reported Tuesday (December 8th). Tadic admitted in court that he took a sip of champagne. Fines were also issued for Sports Minister Snezana Markovic-Samardzic and Belgrade City Assembly President Aleksandar Antic. (B92, Beta, RTS - 08/12/09)
